Scotland's independent schools have a track record of academic excellence, and this was continued in 2018 with another set of excellent exam results, which have only been enhanced by individual and collective successes in sport, art, music and other community enterprises.
With more than 30,000 schoolchildren across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council for Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the best level of service to their schoolchildren and parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their pupils for further and higher education, their chosen careers and their position as world citizens.
As an education sector that can design and implement a tailor-made school curriculum, we see world languages continuing to be a popular and desirable subject in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you talk to someone in a language he understands, it goes to his head.
